Ask HN: Is Motivation the Answer for Everything?
text:
Earning money, is about motivation, and how much you want to earn that money. Becoming famous, is how much enthusiasm you have which is also derived from motivation. Those are just a few examples, and I'm sure there are a lot more.

Is motivation just the answer for happiness, or just, everything other than health? Or I will rephrase it: are we, humans, biologically limited by our own mind? Is the mind of Alex different from Steve?

Ask HN: 'git rebase' searches have gone up. Is company productivity up?
text:
I was curious how the layoffs over the last few months have impacted productivity. Google Trends shows that searches for 'git rebase' have gone up over the last 12 months (https://trends.google.com/trends/explore?date=today%205-y&geo=US&q=git%20rebase). Quite significantly as compared to the year prior.

It's a crude metric and probably actually measures activity vs productivity. So... has productivity / activity increased at your company over the last few months?
